-- Barclays Sells 1.77 Billion Rand of Discount Uridashi Notes
-- B y   H a r u m i   I c h i k u r a
-- 2011-12-28T10:22:45Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-28/barclays-sells-1-77-billion-rand-of-discount-uridashi-notes.html
The following uridashi bond went
on sale. Uridashi bonds are debt issued in the euromarket
and sold mainly to Japanese individual investors.  Issuer:            Barclays Bank Plc.
Amount:            1,770 million South African Rand
Coupon:            0.50 percent of face value
Issue Price:       59.52 percent of face value
Duration:          7 years
Sales period:      Jan. 4 - Jan. 24
Settlement date:   Jan. 25, 2012
Maturity:          Jan. 25, 2019
Uridashi Manager:  SMBC Friend Securities Co.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Harumi Ichikura in London at   hichikura@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Marco Babic at   mbabic@bloomberg.net  